<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1437,795,1434]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,437,795,822]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Recognition characters:</emphasis>
Grayish black species; length 
<quantity box="[783,879,796,822]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8 mm</quantity>
; mystax of males white, females’ mystax entirely black with stouter bristles; thorax gray pollinose; scutellum grayish tomentose with fine white setae and 4 black marginal bristles; wings hyaline; abdomen black, anterior margins of segments 2–7 dorsally gray pollinose, with constrictions in middle on 2–5 and divided at middle on 6 and 7; legs black with white setae and bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1437,795,1434]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,939,966]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Distribution:</emphasis>
