<emphasis box="[507,774,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Backomyia seminoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found only in the type locality in wind-protected gullies on a south slope of the eastern edge of the Seminoe Mountains” (see 
